---
import PageIntro from "../components/PageIntro.astro";
import TrustNote from "../components/TrustNote.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<BaseLayout title="Rastion • Contribute" description="Repo workflow for adding a TSP solver card, running the suites, and regenerating public data." canonical="/contribute/">
  <PageIntro
    eyebrow="Contribute"
    title="Add a TSP solver to Rastion"
    lede="A public listing needs four things: a working adapter, a valid solver card, official suite output, and regenerated site artifacts."
  >
    <TrustNote slot="note" href={`${base}about/#limits`} linkLabel="Current scope">
      The current public flow covers TSP only and publishes suite-scoped results.
    </TrustNote>
  </PageIntro>

  <section class="section-block">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="kicker">Workflow</p>
      <h2>Current repo-verified path</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="destination-grid">
      <article class="destination-card">
        <h3>1. Install locally</h3>
        <pre><code>pip install -e ".[dev,ortools]"
rastion --help</code></pre>
        <p>This installs the local development and optional OR-Tools dependencies used by the release flow.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="destination-card">
        <h3>2. Add the adapter</h3>
        <p>Create a local plugin under <code>plugins_local/</code> that exposes <code>get_solver()</code> and supports <code>tsp</code>.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="destination-card">
        <h3>3. Add the card and README</h3>
        <p>Create <code>catalog/solvers/&lt;solver-id&gt;/card.json</code> and <code>catalog/solvers/&lt;solver-id&gt;/README.md</code>.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="destination-card">
        <h3>4. Validate</h3>
        <pre><code>rastion validate-cards</code></pre>
        <p>Validation checks ids, adapter paths, discoverability, and required detail markdown.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="destination-card">
        <h3>5. Run the official suites</h3>
        <pre><code>rastion eval-suite tsplib-small-v1
rastion eval-suite tsplib-medium-v1
rastion eval-suite tsplib-large-v1</code></pre>
      </article>
      <article class="destination-card">
        <h3>6. Regenerate site data</h3>
        <pre><code>./scripts/release_smoke.sh
cd web && npm run build</code></pre>
        <p>Verify that the solver appears in the catalog, suite output, solver detail page, and TSPLIB arena export.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-block grid grid-two">
    <article class="section-panel">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="kicker">PR expectations</p>
        <h2>What to include in a public listing</h2>
      </div>
      <ul class="list-reset">
        <li>Include the adapter, solver card, README, and generated artifacts.</li>
        <li>Keep method class, dependency requirements, limits, and failure modes visible.</li>
        <li>Keep claims aligned with the published suite results and artifact output.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="section-panel">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="kicker">Scope</p>
        <h2>Current public contract</h2>
      </div>
      <ul class="list-reset">
        <li>v0.1 public listings are TSP only.</li>
        <li>Future work beyond TSP is intentionally outside the current release.</li>
        <li>Official leaderboards stay tied to the curated suite set.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
